Description: AIMS OS — GNOME desktop, installer and user applications
 This metapackage installs the AIMS OS user-facing layer: the GNOME
 desktop (task-gnome-desktop scope — desktop shell, GDM, Files, Web,
 Terminal — without the gnome metapackage's games and bloat), the
 Calamares graphical installer plus its Debian settings, the Plymouth
 boot splash framework (themed by aims-os-branding), Firefox ESR and
 Chromium with French and English locales, the complete LibreOffice
 suite with French and English dictionaries and thesauri, the standard
 GNOME tools (Evince, GIMP, Inkscape, Shotwell, VLC, GNOME Text
 Editor, Evolution), Flatpak with the GNOME Software plugin (Flathub
 remote registered by an AIMS-specific first-boot service), the
 NetworkManager stack with OpenVPN support, a small set of useful
 utilities (KeepassXC, ghostwriter, fish, zsh, ripgrep, fzf, bat,
 p7zip, screenshots), and the GStreamer codecs for media playback.
 .
 The fr_FR.UTF-8 locale and Africa/Dakar timezone are configured at
 the system level by aims-os-core; this metapackage adds the matching
 French desktop locales for LibreOffice, Firefox, hunspell, hyphen
 and mythes.
